==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cordelier
<hw>Cor`de*lier"</hw> <pr>(k⟦ocir⟧r`d⟦esl⟧*l⟦emac⟧r")</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. OF. <ets>cordel</ets>, F.
<ets>cordeau</ets>, dim. fr. <ets>corde</ets> string, rope. See
<er>Cord</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld> <def>A
Franciscan; -- so called in France from the girdle of knotted cord worn
by all Franciscans.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Fr. Hist.)</fld> <def>A member of a French
political club of the time of the first Revolution, of which Danton and
Marat were members, and which met in an old Cordelier convent in
Paris.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cordeling</ent>⟦br⟧
